111.query:
// This query is a tricky one and there are a few things that need to be considered.
// First, the interval needs to be set to 1m for this query. That is required because otherwise the `end()` and `start()` methods will return the start and end timestamp of the interval for which data is rolled up.
// That means: if the interval is 1 minute, start() and end() values will be 1m apart.
// Also means: if the interval is 6 hours, start() and end() values will be 6h apart. 
// The query works by finding the latest bucket that has data in it and taking the start time from it.
// That means: if the interval is higher than 1m, we cant tell how long ago the data was recorded. 
// E.g., if the interval is 6h, we know that there was data one 6h bucket, but there is no way to tell *when* in the 6h timeframe the data was recorded.
// With 1m intervals, we can tell that somewhere in that minute bucket, data was recorded.
// In order to get 1m resolution, this query looks at the last 24h only and forces 1m buckets.

// add the interval start times by using start(). Also fix the timeframe and interval.
timeseries 
  {
    count=count(otelcol_process_uptime), 
    intervalStart=start()
  }, 
  by: { service.name, service.instance.id, k8s.pod.name }, 
  filter: { in(service.name, $CollectorServiceNames) },
  from:-24h, to:now(), 
  interval:1m
| fieldsAdd countIsNull=isNull(count[])                                              // find which buckets have values. null means no value has been recorded into that bucket.
| fieldsAdd lastNonNullIdx = arrayLastIndexOf(countIsNull, false)                    // find the index of the last bucket that is not null, meaning the last bucket that has a value
| fieldsAdd startTimesAndIdx=record(index=iIndex(), startTime=intervalStart[])       // create a record that contains the interval start times and and index
| expand startTimesAndIdx                                                            // expand the records to be able to filter
| filter startTimesAndIdx[index]==lastNonNullIdx                                     // keep only the interval start time for the last bucket that has a value
| fieldsAdd lastWrittenAfter = startTimesAndIdx[startTime]                        // extract the start time and add it as a column to the result
| fieldsAdd `Last Seen`=now()-lastWrittenAfter                                 // calculate how long ago the collector was last seen.
| sort `Last Seen` asc
| fieldsKeep service.name, service.instance.id, `Last Seen`
| limit 100

